l                                     macro                                    l

NAME
     ll - UNIX file listing

SYNOPSIS

     ll [[ooppttiioonnss]] [[ffiilleess ...... ]]

DESCRIPTION

     The ll macro executes the UNIX command llss --ll in the current directory.  Some
     of the more useful options to llss are:

     --tt Sort by last-modification time.

     --uu Sort by last-access time.

     --rr Reverse the sort order.

     --RR Recursively descend directories and list.

DEFINITION

     ddeeff ll ''uunniixx((""llss --ll $$**""))''

EXAMPLE

     ll --uutt ddoo..**

SEE ALSO

     UUNNIIXX UUsseerr RReeffeerreennccee MMaannuuaall

